file.title: AMM PART II-1285 - CHAPTER 06-20-00-01 - AIRCRAFT STATION DIAGRAM - COMPONENT LOCATION

page.data: AIRCRAFT MAINTENANCE MANUAL AIRCRAFT STATION DIAGRAM - COMPONENT LOCATION EFFECTIVITY: ALL 1. General A. The aircraft station diagrams include diagrams of the stations of: body (fuselage), vertical stabilizer, horizontal stabilizer, wing, pylon and nacelle. B. The diagrams show a reference system which gives the location of the structural components in relation to the datum planes.
